des-base.notion","typeVersion":2.2,"position":[8721,1420],"id":"40f5ef8d-8e1c-4ff0-927c-97e119169026","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Daily Schedule\n\nStarts the workflow on a timer — daily at 17:00. No input data; downstream nodes fetch what they need.\n\nNext: Read Recent from Google Sheets","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"756aa1a4-9f03-3a4f-2177-f555b4d529b8","name":"Note: Daily Schedule"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Read Recent from Google Sheets\n\ngoogleSheets — `read` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Newest First · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"07c2a3e4-9a87-5892-a9dc-b45d89fc06b0","name":"Note: Read Recent from Google Sheets"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Trim to Digest Size","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"f2e38314-7800-8eaf-aa0e-2ede4358267e","name":"Note: Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Trim to Digest Size\n\nCaps the stream at 15 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Summarize Content (AI)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"32f6a28d-991f-119c-375b-32fd96cea131","name":"Note: Trim to Digest Size"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Content (AI)\n\nMap-reduce summarization chain — handles long content without blowing the context window.\n\nPorts: ①→ Post Digest to Gmail · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,520],"id":"5dd2e48c-a5d9-8ab7-1f17-909b9aac1a94","name":"Note: Summarize Content (AI)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Groq Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `llama-3.3-70b-versatile`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Summarize Content (AI)** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 Groq API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,1090],"id":"361cc313-0df5-fd4b-1dbe-781e25db3810","name":"Note: Groq Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Post Digest to Gmail\n\ngmail — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Archive Digest in Google Sheets · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1533,520],"id":"71a6611f-0610-db6b-2905-e0879c1eb935","name":"Note: Post Digest to Gmail"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Digest in Google Sheets\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Serialize Run Output (CSV) · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1857,520],"id":"78e94e50-4dac-081c-47f0-2c4599963f56","name":"Note: Archive Digest in Google Sheets"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2181,520],"id":"00df9bbf-700a-5d62-2503-0de7fbe5a8e1","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Stamp Completion Time · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2505,520],"id":"c5db51fd-239f-9c70-2867-9418b8ad4cb4","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2829,520],"id":"4ea3c472-41b3-9fe5-0a1f-5c238ca80f1c","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3153,520],"id":"673330c7-f857-6c9c-8c69-70cb694c3741","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3477,520],"id":"08ea7284-bd70-4c31-6f08-4ca9a74bcb71","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3801,520],"id":"a3fea83c-c846-c436-af04-1a9b431626ae","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `read` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4125,520],"id":"f799565f-d384-5425-94ea-1ff3d2868647","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4449,520],"id":"aaba45bf-af23-3cf4-c3f2-9e8094fec7eb","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,520],"id":"05468e98-9f11-c020-3153-5cd32c92982b","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,520],"id":"89618743-7ade-4e38-2a47-f1d6ba6b738c","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per email (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,520],"id":"4091a517-026d-7805-2e7b-4a714d47946e","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Stamp Processing Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5745,520],"id":"c02f38b8-e681-3ddb-8352-913d3874e76b","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Processing Time\n\nStamps `processedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6069,520],"id":"4d3ce02c-836c-3ec7-bd00-918d14a9d9a4","name":"Note: Stamp Processing Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Sort Emails Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6393,520],"id":"fe1f0db6-4aa0-624f-e37b-2a06d754ee16","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Emails Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6717,520],"id":"2f6ea4ce-334e-b9ee-6552-c404a5647819","name":"Note: Sort Emails Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Tag Pipeline Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7041,520],"id":"666cf627-8043-ecac-dd71-dd3555e9b2fd","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\nShapes the item: writes `pipeline`, `version`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7365,520],"id":"f5cbc6ea-e50c-4911-a2d2-210362fb3580","name":"Note: Tag Pipeline Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 50 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7689,520],"id":"22536ba6-9bd6-f2ed-2e53-e1cb661e1f45","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8013,520],"id":"3a0cd58a-4614-3ead-26a8-9237a0fbb3cb","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8337,520],"id":"c047f8fc-8092-9311-e7cb-bb20d91a8ed2","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8661,520],"id":"f8599d26-52e1-5543-5838-13d065d9dc47","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8013,1540],"id":"bc72f212-bc79-dbb4-6a3b-b7c53079e9ff","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8337,1540],"id":"60333c5b-1608-8cc0-7294-637cc2d37767","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8661,1540],"id":"d3b9829e-cdf7-228a-8de9-5e2b5ee2f73c","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Send a metrics report with Google Sheets and Gmail\n\n**Pattern:** Scheduled Digest · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nSend a metrics report with Google Sheets and Gmail. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual inbox triage is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nDaily Schedule → Read Recent from Google Sheets → Newest First → Trim to Digest Size → Summarize Content (AI) → Post Digest to Gmail → Archive Digest in Google Sheets → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to scheduled digest without manual effort\n- Anyone automating inbox triage in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; Groq API key; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"f929e457-8408-6d51-a1c0-08a98cb28af1","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-20],"id":"53e84015-2008-0da0-35db-73d57c786c60","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-20],"id":"a1293495-2a63-255b-4cec-34f0f995a083","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-20],"id":"bae3808b-2172-f901-f170-7b6e15fa64ff","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your inbox triage process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-20],"id":"7de29342-f541-73f2-dc6f-235a9c39d76e","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Daily Schedule":{"main":[[{"node":"Read Recent from Google Sheets","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Read Recent from Google Sheets":{"main":[[{"node":"Newest First","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Trim to Digest Size","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Trim to Digest Size":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Content (AI)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Groq Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Summarize Content (AI)","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Summarize Content (AI)":{"main":[[{"node":"Post Digest to Gmail","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Post Digest to Gmail":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Digest in Google Sheets","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Digest in Google Sheets":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Processing Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Processing Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Emails Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Emails Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Tag Pipeline Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Tag Pipeline Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"30b7cbf8-0826-4bbe-a0bc-9d795a663930","id":"FDX02392"}